00:00:01.230 --> 00:00:02.380
GOPI KALLAYIL: Good afternoon.

00:00:02.380 --> 00:00:05.710
We live in an astonishingly
interesting time in that of

00:00:05.710 --> 00:00:08.370
the 7 billion people on the
planet, 2 billion are on the

00:00:08.370 --> 00:00:13.020
internet and 6 billion
have cellphones.

00:00:13.020 --> 00:00:14.630
So this has become the
most pervasive

00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:16.050
technology in human history.

00:00:16.050 --> 00:00:19.890
More people carry one of these
devices than have access to

00:00:19.890 --> 00:00:22.720
clean drinking water
or electricity.

00:00:22.720 --> 00:00:26.700
And arguably, all of this
technology in humanity has

00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:30.470
increased the productivity,
but it also means we are

00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:33.050
drowning in the information that
comes towards us through

00:00:33.050 --> 00:00:34.480
these technologies.

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:38.290
The amount of email that keeps
flooding towards us and the

00:00:38.290 --> 00:00:43.210
extent to which our lives are
now accessed by other people

00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:45.770
sending us information through
all of these media, whether

00:00:45.770 --> 00:00:49.460
it's text, or email,
or other means.

00:00:49.460 --> 00:00:52.380
So on the one hand, it does
increase productivity, on the

00:00:52.380 --> 00:00:55.750
other hand, we also
feel overwhelmed.

00:00:55.750 --> 00:01:00.730
Into this field has stepped in
Jared Goralnick, one of the

00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.390
foremost experts on how do we
live a more productive, sane,

00:01:05.390 --> 00:01:08.780
and happier life while still
using all of these

00:01:08.780 --> 00:01:09.500
technologies.

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:12.440
In fact, Jared was so convinced
about this topic

00:01:12.440 --> 00:01:17.100
that he has become part of the
leadership team at the

00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:20.310
Information Overload
Research Group.

00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:21.670
He founded two companies.

00:01:21.670 --> 00:01:25.590
