Has somebody ever sent you
that calendar invite?

00:25:57.460 --> 00:25:59.850
How useful is that to you?

00:25:59.850 --> 00:26:00.940
We all do that.

00:26:00.940 --> 00:26:03.050
Well, actually, I don't do that
anymore, it's terrible.

00:26:03.050 --> 00:26:04.620
I laugh at people when
they do that.

00:26:04.620 --> 00:26:07.170
Every single time I create an
appointment, I put what kind

00:26:07.170 --> 00:26:10.720
of appointment it is, coffee,
Skype, lunch, colon.

00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:14.880
And then I put my name first
and then I put their name.

00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:17.010
And they love that and it looks
great in their calendar.

00:26:17.010 --> 00:26:18.200
They know what's going on.

00:26:18.200 --> 00:26:20.430
It indicates whether you need
to be somewhere else or

00:26:20.430 --> 00:26:23.170
whether you don't need to be,
whether you need video or not.

00:26:23.170 --> 00:26:26.290
But the main thing is never
ever create a meeting.

00:26:26.290 --> 00:26:28.710
I would never email Trevor and
say meeting with Trevor

00:26:28.710 --> 00:26:31.880
because he has to then look into
the attendee list to find

00:26:31.880 --> 00:26:32.910
out who I am.

00:26:32.910 --> 00:26:34.270
And I had a meeting with
somebody the other day where

00:26:34.270 --> 00:26:36.710
they did that and their Gmail
address was instructively.

00:26:36.710 --> 00:26:39.160
I didn't even know
who they were.

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:41.220
So that is my calendar tip.

00:26:41.220 --> 00:26:45.120
Always indicate what type of
meeting it is, put your name,

00:26:45.120 --> 00:26:49.010
if you need to, parentheses
Google, dash their name, if

00:26:49.010 --> 00:26:50.950
you need to, parentheses
their company.

