00:30:24.110 --> 00:30:26.690
So the thing that you really
need to do that's on your big

00:30:26.690 --> 00:30:28.490
list, you can use your
calendar for that.

00:30:28.490 --> 00:30:29.900
You can say, two hours.

00:30:29.900 --> 00:30:31.650
Or you can say like what I do,
I just know that it's my

00:30:31.650 --> 00:30:33.330
mornings is going
to be my really,

00:30:33.330 --> 00:30:34.510
really important stuff.

00:30:34.510 --> 00:30:37.410
So recognizing that when I look
for what I'm going to do

00:30:37.410 --> 00:30:39.400
tomorrow, something
really important

00:30:39.400 --> 00:30:41.120
has to happen tomorrow.

00:30:41.120 --> 00:30:43.810
And then, if necessary,
block that time out.

00:30:43.810 --> 00:30:45.570
Or if you just generally
understand how your schedule

00:30:45.570 --> 00:30:46.520
works, then don't.

00:30:46.520 --> 00:30:49.000
And then spend your time on
little to-do list stuff.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:51.080
The five minute things I like
